---
title: Chicken Katsu with Sesame-Dressed Cucumber & Jasmine Rice
description: Crispy chicken may just be the world’s most beloved food. Hear us out: Southern-fried, milanese, schnitzel, kiev—all types of crispy chicken from all corners of the world. True to form, this Japanese-style rendition is comforting and delicious. Here, chicken is pounded thin, coated in panko and cornstarch, then flash-fried to light and crunchy perfection. On the side is a classic katsu dipping sauce plus crunchy sesame-marinated cucumber and buttery jasmine rice. The results, unsurprisingly, are impressively tasty (and crispy as all get-out).
